# Design Review v1.0

## Purpose

This document summarizes the design review of version **1.0** and confirms the readiness of the software architecture for the first hardware tests.

---

## Completed Work

Version 1.0 includes:

* MIDI message processing module;
* keyboard state management module;
* 74HC595 shift register driver;
* main program loop;
* modular firmware architecture;
* complete technical documentation.

---

## Verified Design

The following aspects have been reviewed:

* overall software architecture;
* interaction between software modules;
* MIDI message processing logic;
* keyboard buffer implementation;
* SPI communication with the shift register chain;
* public interfaces of all modules.

---

## Architectural Principles

The following principles have been verified:

* one module — one responsibility;
* minimal coupling between modules;
* simple and stable public interfaces;
* no duplicated functionality;
* independent module development.

---

## Known Limitations

Version 1.0 intentionally provides a limited feature set.

Currently implemented:

* MIDI Note On;
* MIDI Note Off;
* single MIDI channel;
* fixed keyboard size;
* Arduino Uno support.

Velocity, selectable MIDI channels and additional features are planned for future releases.

---

## Hardware Test Readiness

The software design has successfully completed a logical review.

The firmware architecture is complete.

The project is ready for the first hardware validation.

The following items should be verified during hardware testing:

* MIDI message reception;
* SPI communication;
* data transfer to the 74HC595 shift register chain;
* correct keyboard contact emulation;
* overall system stability.

---

## Future Development

Future versions will extend the available functionality while preserving the existing modular architecture.

